THE AAC IS OPEN BY APPOINTMENT ONLY!
To set up a meet and greet, please fill out a dog adoption application ASAP or if you have already submitted one with us, call/email to put your name in line. We will form a line like usual based on who has an active and approved application in. We will go through our line to set up a private meet and greet for potential adopters to foster.
307-739-1881
adopt@animaladoptioncenter.org

https://form.jotform.com/42994530730154

Gimli
5 month old, male, Reservation mix, medium size
Meet Gimli! Gimli describes a reservation mutt and is likely made up of 5+ breeds to make his cute face. He will likely be about medium size and we can speculate 40-60lbs. He was found as a stray on the Wind River Reservation and no one came to claim him at the Paws For Life Riverton shelter. He is still a young puppy and will benefit from an owner willing to put in some basic training. He has done well with all walks of life so far and is going to make a great companion!

Please note, Animal Adoption Center cannot guarantee the breed, composition or ages of our dogs as we usually have no history prior to them entering the rescue. We make every effort to ensure the dogs are healthy.

Please know that our intention is to insure long lasting committed homes for the animals at the AAC. If we feel that an animal and a potential owner are not a good fit we reserve the right to refuse adoption.

animal.description:
* PLEASE READ DESCRIPTION FULLY BEFORE APPLYING THROUGH OUR WEBSITE BIGLOVEANIMALRESCUE.ORG **


**The adoption fee is $500. Our rescue covers microchip, vaccinations to her adoption date, and spaying at one of our veterinarians when she's old enough.

Meet Riley!!! Riley is an eleven-month-old female Lab mix pup! She has lots of energy and she LOVES to snuggle ?She enjoys going on walks and is really good at sitting before crossing the street ?? Her hobbies include fetching, playing with other dogs, licking the peanut butter out of a hollow bone, stealing my spot on the bed then refusing to move, waking her fosters up in the morning by licking their faces, and following them everywhere they go (an adorable stage 5 clinger”) ?

Riley had a rough start to life ? She had owners who isolated her from any contact for most of her life.  She was then surrendered to us when they didn’t have time for her anymore ? As a result, she can get a little scared when she meets new people and sometimes nervous when going on walks at night or when she hears unfamiliar sounds. Her fosters started doing basic training with her and she’s so eager to learn more.  She thrives with constant affection and gives it in return. We are looking for a family for Riley who has a backyard, doggy sibling and will continue to work with her and gain her love and trust


**If you're interested in Riley, you must visit our website and fill out an application here: https://bigloveanimalrescue.org/adoption-application-form/

**No meet and greets prior to approved application.

**Due to the volume of messages we receive on all of our platforms, we do NOT send follow up emails to our applicants and do not reply to messages here on PetFinder. We’re a small, volunteer ran rescue so we can only do so much in 24 hours. Thank you for understanding!

Again, please no repeat emails. If we feel you're the right fit, we will contact you.

www.bigloveanimalrescue.org

animal.description:
JETT

Gorgi / Beagle Mix |

Small (22-25 lbs.)

| 3-4 Years Old / Spayed Female | Accepting Applications for Adoption

Hi! My name is
Jett
! I'm about 3-4 years old and I'm a Corgi/Beagle mix. I've got the body of a Corgi, (including the large ears and deliciously juicy thighs), with Beagle markings.

My foster Mom says I'm a good girl because I'm house
trained, good

with other dogs and leash

trained! I love to go for walks but get a little anxious on car rides.

I love a lot of things, for instance, WATER!! I love to play with it and get all wet! I also LOVE TOYS, there are these special ones my foster parents got me that I love to chase, retrieve and just keep in my mouth. Sometimes I ever fall asleep with it in my mouth. I love to snuggle on the couch and one the bed. Oh and food...yeah, food is definitely a favorite. Plus I'm a sucker for treats!

Of course, I'm not perfect, I lick the ground when I get anxious.

My fosters have tried working with me but it is what it is. We all can't be perfect. I've also got quite the sniffer, m

y humans swear I can smell a flea fart in the wind.

All in all, I am a happy girl that loves to play and snuggle. I sleep in my own bed but it's a real treat when my humans allow me in bed with them. I enjoy walks, my toys, treats and playing in water. I get along well with other dogs and I'm curious about cats.

If you're looking for an all around happy girl who loves to cuddle, please visit idohr.org and complete an adoption application.

Please visit our website if you would like to submit an adoption application.

Jett's Adoption Donation Fee is $325. Jett i

s spayed, current on all vaccinations, has received a wellness exam and is microchipped.

I Dream of Home Rescue, Inc. is a 501(c)(3) Non-Profit Organization.

TAX ID: 81-0780050

I Dream of Home Rescue
PO Box 7612, La Verne, California 91750

www.idohr.org

www.facebook.com/IDOHR.ORG

animal.description:
Please go to www.yvpr.org/adoptions for more information and to complete your application.**  
Large Marge, AKA Margie,  is a 1 1/2 year old Anatolian shepherd mix female that weighs 85 pounds, she is brown colored with a darker muzzle, she has down ears and a wide strip down her back that is wavy and longer. Margie is in foster care with other dogs and puppies of all sizes and ages, she does great with all but she is a quiet girl with lower energy and likes to nap a lot and keep you company, she loves her mealtimes and is treat motivated, we do not know if she has met a cat and she is a super EASY KEEPER...she is great with all people and will be a wonderful family member. Margie will follow along slowly on a leash and she is a 100% house trained, spayed, micro chipped with all vaccinations, she is ready to go to her forever home and get all the love and pets she deserves. 


An application must be filled out and accepted before a meet can be set up. If accepted, you will hear from us within 72 hours. You will have the opportunity to ask questions before you meet the pet; an adoption may or may not happen at that time. We do adopt outside the Yakima area IF you are able to come to Yakima to pick up your adopted pet.  We do not have a kennel facility; all of our pets are in foster homes. Therefore, meets and adoptions take place at either our office or at a place chosen by the foster.   If a pet has 'pending' beside its name, an adoption is imminent. Please fill out an application anyway because adoptions don't always go through. Your application will be kept on file for 30 days in case you find another pet you'd like to apply for.  Thanks for thinking adoption and Good Luck!

animal.description: PACC is a pretty casual place, but every once in a while, we get a dog that's worth a little more formality. Meet Mr. Max. Mr. Max is a handsome, senior guy who came to PACC with some medical issues. He's healing up, but he'd sure like to finish up his recovery in a soft, comfy home instead of the shelter. He also spent some time in PACC's decompression program for shy and scared dogs, but he's come a long way. In play group, Mr. Max was appropriate with his greetings and tolerant of the young whippersnappers that wanted to meet him. He wasn't too interested in affection from his handlers and mostly kept to himself and explored the yard. Mr. Max is a very special older gentleman who is looking for a very special person to call his own. He can be a bit cranky, but we know he's a big softie inside and would love to get out of the shelter and into a home. If you can help him out, make an appointment to meet him today.

animal.description:
Meet Lindi! A beautiful sight hound from the Middle East!

Red Collar was contacted by a rescue group in Oman.  They take in Wadi dogs - dogs that are descended from the Saluki breed and native to the Middle East.  In Oman there are no animal control shelters for stray dogs, and they are generally just shot by the police.  This small rescue group takes in as many Wadi dogs as they can, and sends them to rescues in Europe and North America.  One of their volunteers was flying to Houston and brought Lindi to us.

Lindi is a sweet girl and loves people and other dogs.  Her foster mom in Oman was a dog trainer, so Linid is very well trained.

Lindi is very active and loves to play with other dogs.  We require her new home have another dog for her to play with.  She also needs a large yard in a quiet suburban or country setting.  City noises makes her uncomfortable.

Lindi loves to cuddle and has an adorable curly tail.

For more information, please contact info@redcollar.org.
Adoption applications can be submitted on our website, redcollar.org.

Age - 1 year
Weight - 35 lbs.
Dogs - yes required
Cats - no
Kids - older kids okay
Vaccinated - yes
Spayed - yes
Microchipped - yes

Our adoption process typically takes from one to two weeks. When you find an animal you are interested in, we ask that you fill out an application as a first step so we can determine if your family is a good fit for the animal. If you are, then we will contact you to arrange a time for you and your family to meet the animal so you can decide if it is a good fit. If you currently have dogs, we require that the dogs be present at the meeting to make sure it's a good fit all around. Once compatibility is determined, we move on to the paperwork and finalizing the adoption. 

If the meet is not a good fit, we will keep your application on file for up to 1 year and we will gladly consider your family for another dog.

MARL ARRIVAL: The S-Litter was surrendered to MARL because their owner could no longer care for them.

The S-Litter will need to continue getting medicated baths and oral medication until their skin is cleared by a MARL veterinarian. animal.description:
Meet Gullivere! 

He is a one year old Pit Bull mix who weighs about 45 pounds. He is a sensitive boy that can be shy when first meeting new people, but once he warms up is a goofy boy who loves to play! Squeaky toys are the way to his heart, and he can't get enough of them. Gullivere recently had a femoral head osteotomy, so he would love some extra TLC in his new home! To help his recovery, he'd love going on slow walks and dancing on his rear legs can help strengthen his legs and speed up his recovery! Due to his shy nature, if there are children in his future home, they would need to be ages 13 and up. Gullivere can be dog selective so he would prefer to be the only dog in the home so that he can get all of your love! 

If this lovable guy is pulling at your heart strings, give us a call to schedule an appointment to meet him today!

animal.description:
Howdy! My name's Rowdy! I'm an English Coonhound mix, 7 years old, 80 lbs, & I have a Redtick coloring.

I'm a Southern boy who's jumped around a bit. You could say I'm a driftin' cowboy. Originally from Georgia, plenty of rainy nights there, then I was over in South Carolina for a while, & now I'm up here in Minnesota. Let me tell ya, coming here in January may be the dumbest thing I've ever done! How do y'all LIVE like this!? & you're telling me this year is actually a mild Winter compared to most? How is a country boy supposed to survive!?I shoulda went out West to find me some Hollywood honeys! Oh well, beggars can't be choosers & all that, I guess. I can't change my tune now! Anyway, enough complainin'. Let me tell y'all a bit about myself. Now, I may be old in years, but I'm young at heart! I've still got plenty of kick left in my old bones! Obviously, being a hound, I've got a nose that never stops, so I'm always on the move & ready to go. So I'm more than capable of keeping up with whatever action you've got goin' on. Heck, I could probably still outlasy plenty of you young'ns! Although, I've had to sit in a kennel most days lately goin' from shelter to shelter, so I've been singin' the blues, but I'm still pretty positive most days! I'm not a huge fan of other animals, though. I definitely don't like cats, & I don't really get along with other dogs all that well either. Maybe the ones I've interacted with so far just haven't meshed well with me, but it'd probably be best if I was a one-animal guy. Overall, I'm just a lively guy lookin' for a new family to help settle down in this tundra I'm gonna have to get used to callin' home. I'd be a great exercise partner, family dog, whatever ya need!

I'm up to date on shots, neutered, chipped, & ready to go! A also tested negative for heartworm. Come on over tonight & get yourself a Rowdy friend!

animal.description:
Meet Tugz 
This female six month old puppers is a SWEETIE. It’s hard to tell what she is, but our best guess would say she is a Lab/Husky mix, mix, mix, lol! We just know she is very pretty, with a beautiful creamy colored coat, gorgeous green eyes and expressive ears. She is still small at 27 lbs., but she might top out around 40lbs. So hard to say, but she is still pretty small. We rescued Tugz from a high kill shelter and brought her to the safety of ours. She is a lovely girl and is going to make for a wonderful family companion. 
Tugz loves to play and is a lot of fun. She’s left her past behind and relishes playing tug and running around. Tugz also loves to settle in a lap and be loved on. She’s a blend of innocence and fun, sweet and smart. Tugz seems dog friendly and welcomes every opportunity to get out of her kennel to play and explore. She loves her toys too! She is afraid of cats, but we are hopeful she might get used to one if introduced slowly. Tugz enjoys being with people, she’s very social and she shows us every day how grateful she is that she’s been saved. Such a love!
Tugz travels well in a car and enjoys going on rides. We can’t say enough good things about Tugz. If you are looking for a terrific young dog to welcome to your heart and home, Tugz may be for you. She will give you her whole heart and make your life that much better. She brightens our days and we know she will brighten yours. She’s a little gem. 
If interested in Tugz, please submit an application online at: https://www.charlessmithgallhumanesociety.org/page/dog-adoption-application 
Once an application is submitted online, you will receive an email saying your application has been successfully submitted.  If you don’t receive this email within 24 hours, please check to make sure all application fields were completed or please call our shelter at 706-865-4135. All adopters must complete an approval process which involves a reference check with current/recent vet and a brief home visit if located in the immediate area. We do permit out of state adoptions. Adopters MUST come to the shelter to transport their new family member home. We do not ship nor do we transport them to their new homes. Adoption policies and application procedures are detailed at the shelter website: http://smithgallhumanesociety.org/ under tab All Adoptable Animals.
Charles Smithgall Humane Society (CSHS) is a No kill shelter. Animals in our care remain safe with us until adopted. Resident animals are primarily owner relinquished and also accepted from local Animal Control. The facility usually is operating at capacity with a list of animals waiting for space to open.
Adoptions and meet and greets are being scheduled by appointment only. Please call our office, email us or complete an application and someone will be in touch just as soon as they can. 
Location: 4823 Helen Hwy., Sautee, GA 30571, Phone: 706-865-4135
Email: smithgallhumanesociety@windstream.net
Our shelter in Sautee GA is located about 3 miles south of the alpine town of Helen in northeast GA.

Name: Brixton
Weight: 38lbs
Age: 3 years
Gender: Male
Spayed/Neutered: Neutered
Breed: Boxer mix
Color: Tan and white

Crate size recommended: medium

Good with women: yes
Good with men: yes
Good with kids: would not recommend
Good with other dogs: even though he lived with a pile of other dogs he is not good with other dogs
Good with cats: no
House trained: appears he lived outside mostly, but doing well with house training
Crate trained: yes
Energy level: medium
Can be handled/touched: yes provided not invasive as it makes him nervous—for example, we expressed his anal glands, did not appreciate that at all. Vet type stuff. Would probably need to be muzzled at the vet
Barker: no
Flight risk: no likes to be w/ people
Food aggressive: has probably been in competition for food all his life; will guard his food
Current food: whole earth farms adult recipe (chicken and whitefish)
Walks on leash: yes
Leash reactive to people or dogs: would not love a dog to come up and get right in his face but he’s fine passing other dogs on a leash; loves people
Rides well in car: has always been crated and does well
Destructive: removed jacket and ate a bed for lack of something better to entertain himself with at the time but not destructive as a whole
Needs a home with a yard: would be nice
Needs a home with another dog: No
Can live in an apartment: could provided he received adequate exercise

History (how did you acquire dog?): Brixton was one of three bigger dogs who lived mostly outside a home with 28 dogs total. The majority of the dogs were Chihuahua terrier types and under 10 pounds. We took all 28 of those dogs and have placed several of them. Brixton had severe flea dermatitis and his coat was a mess. He was also heartworm positive?but has been treated

Brixton is so incredibly sweet and affectionate. If you are looking for a best bud and you have no pets or young kids he is your man!

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Macaroni, but you can just call me Mac. I'm a pit/boxer mix, 2 years old, 56 lbs, & I have a tan & white coloring.

I'll let you know right now that I can be a VERY stubborn boy! I need a lot of training when it comes to manners, leash-walking, & especially with not using my mouth so much. I'm a super rough player, & my very first instinct is to start biting. Not in a break skin sort of intention, but I've definitely left plenty of marks & bruises on people. Which is why I wouldn't be good in a home with small kids. I could easily injure a smaller person like that without even trying because I get so carried away. & similar to Wanda, another dog I came here with, I get really rough when it comes to other animals as well, so that could end badly if I'm with another dog & I get too aggressive with them while playing & they take it the wrong way. I'll definitely need someone who's willing to take an "Alpha" role over me. I might be stubborn, but I listen very well if I have a strict owner who knows what they're doing when it comes to training & doesn't put up with any BS! I'll easily take on the role of a follower if I have someone who's willing to put in the effort & be my leader. I'm the kinda guy who needs structure, not just any old family or owner will do! That's not to say I couldn't be a family dog of course, but I'll definitely need something to keep me busy & kept on a short leash so to speak until I learn my manners. I've never been aggressive with people or anything though, just the opposite! I'm a super snuggly & cuddly guy, I just don't really know how to behave myself is all. I've never had enough structure in my life to really know how! I'm definitely not a dog for the faint of heart, & I'll definitely require a lot of effort, but if you're someone who loves to train dogs or likes to challenge themselves, I could use someone just like you!

I'm up to date on shots, neutered, chipped, & ready to go! I also tested negative for heartworm. If you're hungry for some pittie lovin', come get yourself some Macaroni!

***Please DO NOT send us inquiries/emails asking if this dog is still available. If a dog/puppy is still listed on Petfinder- we are still accepting applications for them**

Canello is in a foster home in Houston, TX and can transport to the PNW mid February. 

Canello is the most handsome cuddly boy you'll ever meet! He was listed as 5 years old at the shelter, but we think he might be a little younger because this boy just loves to play! Our best guess at breed is a labrador retriever/pit mix. Canello was confiscated from his owner down in Houston, TX and taken to a high kill shelter. We do not know the circumstances surrounding why he was confiscated, but we imagine they weren't great :(  Canello was heartworm positive, but he has since undergone heartworm treatment to get rid of those yucky worms in his heart! He is now heartworm free & looking for his forever home! Canello was attacked by another dog in his foster home in Houston and ever since, he has not been the same with other pets :( He is very nervous around other dogs. Ever since his attack Canello has made it clear he does NOT like other dogs and will require a home with no other pets. We are willing to pay for 2 sessions with a trainer of our choosing for any adopter to work with. 

Canello is extremely sweet & gentle with children! In his current foster home he likes to play fetch outside with the neighbor's 3 year old. Canello would make a great running buddy and he'll also be your netflix & chill partner as he loves to cuddle up in your lap and sleep! Canello is not a huge fan of the crate, he'll go in it if he must, but he prefers to sit and wait for you by the door until you return home. Canello LOVES his squeaky toys and he loves to destroy them even more! This boy is just a ball of fun and will make the best addition to your family.

***Listed BREED and AGE - We are taking our best guess on age, breed and size when fully grown. We rarely know a dog's exact age nor are we able to tell the true or full breed mix of dogs as our information is limited most of the time.

The first step in our process is filling out an application. We will review your application as soon as we are able- there are two of us and we do the best that we can. We review applications on a first come first serve basis and look for the best fit/match for dog and applicant.

https://heartoftheunderdog.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
Happy Birthday Gary Groot!My siblings and I decided to sponsor this life saving transport to honor our father's 81st birthday. Our father, Gary Groot, is the main reason we are all animal lovers. We grew up watching and learning how to properly pamper our puppies and he instilled in us the importance of adoption; how it saves lives. My father just lost his beloved Precious who he loved with all his heart and took her everywhere, even bought a travel trailer so she could join him on mission projects for the church. Precious was by his side for the last 15 years and will now wait for him at the Rainbow Bridge. Suzanne, Karen & Tom

Lucy and her 5 siblings were born around January 7, 2020, and may top out in the 60-65 pound range. Please understand we are truly guessing on the breed for this family. Some of the siblings have a more Retriever look while others we feel have more of a Collie appearance to them. They are wonderful with the other dogs and adore us, humans. It is likely they did not have much human interaction while growing up and so we anticipate you will have some basic training to do. They are sweet-natured, intelligent, teens, so training should go smoothly. This is all we know so far and we will be learning as we go and so will you.
The Adoption Fee for this dog is $500.00
Adoptions fees vary based on adoptability. In general our fees include spay/neuter, all age appropriate vaccines, Home Again micro-chipping & registration, worming & flea control - a 'complete' pet. We accept CASH or Visa/Mastercard ONLY.

Joyful Rescues has no funding except for our adoption fees and miscellaneous donations. Pet care and vet bills are expensive - you must be ready to take on this financial (as well as emotional) responsibility. YOU MUST BE AT LEAST 25 YEARS OF AGE TO ADOPT A DOG FROM JOYFUL RESCUES

We keep our pet list as up-to-date as possible. As soon as a pet is adopted, it is removed from the list. If a pet is still showing, it is still available for adoption.

Can't Adopt Me? SPONSOR ME
Look for the Link 'Special Instructions to Seller' if you want to note a particular pet
Before you seek to adopt a pet from Joyful Rescues, please read our Pet Adoption page http://www.joyfulrescues.org/pet_adoption.html.

Online Application

animal.description: Hi! I'm Jasmine, and I'm a special girl looking for a special kind of home. You see, I'm super cute but I'm also super shy. It takes me quite a while to warm up to new people. My foster mom and dad have been really kind to me, and have won me over, but it took lots of time and lots of patience. I am food motivated, so bribing me with high value treats is a plus! My ideal home would be one where it is pretty quiet, without a lot of people who come and go. Kids in the home would need to be more in the 12ish and up range, and willing to be slow and gentle when working with me. If I had another dog to live with, I'd want it to be calm and confident. I don't really know how to play with other dogs. At just under 40 pounds, I'm a nice medium size. I'm not a great fit for a lot of homes, but there is the "just right" kind out there...I know it! If you think you might be able to help a sweet girl like me become the dog I was meant to be, we should meet!

Charlotte is a true beauty of a gal!! She is potty/house trained. She is full of great energy and is learning her leash skills. We can see her being a running partner or even go on adventurous hikes. Charlotte Gets along with other dogs at her foster home. No cats just based on her energy as she does not know her own strength. She Loves playing in the water and also being a cuddle bug. animal.description:
Meet baby Blaze!!!

He is a 3 month old German Shepherd/Belgian Malinois mix who is currently in a foster home in Ormond Beach. Blaze is a sweet and playful puppy who is already crate trained and in the process of potty training. He sleeps through the night with no accidents but still tinkles when he sees people and gets excited. He enjoys playing ball and daily belly rubs. Walks well on leash and doesn't mind cuddles (like all the time)

Blaze is fully vaccinated, microchipped and neutered.

Adoption requirements:
1. Must have previous Belgian Malinos experience (other applicants will not be considered)
2. Must work from home or less than 4 hours a day to continue potty training
3. Must own a home with a secure fenced in yard
4. All current pets must be spayed/neutered and up to date on heartworm prevention
5. Home insurance must allow German Shepherd Breed

If you meet those requirement and would like to adopt Blaze, please visit www.dbgsdrescue.org
Send in an application. Once approved, we will schedule a home visit and then a meet and greet with the pup.
His adoption fee is $300

IF YOU SEE THIS POST, IT MEANS HE IS AVAILABLE AND WE ARE ACCEPTING APPLICATIONS. THANK YOU

animal.description:
Please welcome island girl Cora!
This sweet little girl were struggling to survive on the streets as a scared stray little puppy in the Dominican Republic.
A great Samaritan that locally comes to the aid of dogs in need on her island. Took these girls in an contacted rescues in the states for help.
We answered the call and we flew in these girl and many others.
It is now Cora's turn to find her forever home.
She is about 1yrs old. Fully trained. With housebreaking and learning all her commands and household manners.

Cora fosters with her great foster daddy and i learning so much and is areal joy!
She is learning the ropes everyday.

. Cora is fully housebroken and crate trained and is learning her manners too, Cora would like a normal suburb home away from the city and loud noises and traffic. Cora Prefers to be the only furkid in her home! She loves to play with pups outside her home at parks and play dates, but in her home she doesn't want to share her Mom/ Dad or her personal space. Can you Blame her?

You have to to understand these were once street dogs being hit by cars and abused by public kids and poisoned, to then finding rescue with a nice lady on the beach, to Now here in the States with big city noise and such, so lets gives this girl some Peace again! She can still be alittle shyy with new meets and new things but she gets better every day, every week!

Must haves for Cora:

Dog experienced owners, willing to continue the good work our foster dad has done and make Cora a great success story.
Cora will do best in a single person home. She bonds with her 1 human to trust for direction, control and affection. she has a hard time trusting more then her 1 person and has proven little tough in a multi family home.
so Cora would make a great attention to that 1 person to give her a chance!



If you would like to be Cora's hero please email us for an application and Come meet her!
Hemlockedgerescue@yahoo.com

animal.description:
Alvin is one-year old as of mid-Jan, 45-50 lbs, came to us as a stray no one ever came for. He just loves attention, is great with other dogs, NO to cats, just a great young dog seeking a forever family.
ADOPTION FEES Dogs & Puppies.....$100.00 . This Adoption fee includes: mandatory spay/neuter which will be done before you can take your dog or puppy home with you; basic canine immunizations (DHPP-CPV & Bordatella Intranasal); de-wormings; one-year rabies vaccination if old enough; heartworm test if over five months old; microchip from 24-Pet Watch; certificate for free health examination at your participating veterinarian; and a goodie bag chocked full of information, toys, and more.
The first step to do an adoption is to do our Adoption Application here: https://www.elmorehumane.org/adoption-application-online-form2.html
IMPORTANT - we respond to your emailed applications and queries via email back to you. Please make sure you have either added our email (hselco@bellsouth.net) to your contact list or that you routinely check your SPAM folder for our response just to be safe. If we do not receive a timely response we simply move on to another applicant.
Yes, there are sometimes exceptions to our normal fee for older dogs or special cases. Some of our pets have also been lovingly sponsored by caring people and we will let the approved adopter know about that at the point of adoption. Visit our Website at: http://www.elmorehumane.org The staff would also like to remind you that for faster response to inquiries about adoptable animals to have the animals ID#, name & description. This way your questions will be answered in a timely manner.
All pet adoption websites & our shelter management software require that we choose a primary and/or secondary breed for our dogs. While our staff is quite breed knowledgeable, in many cases we are truly making our best guesses as to their breed(s) based on many factors but cannot promise that what we have said is accurate. So taking into account your own parameters for things such as size, coat care, activity level, etc please come and get to know our dog(s) as individuals to see if their personalities and yours are a forever match.
Phone: (334) 567-3377 Fax: (334) 567-8774 E-mail: hselco@bellsouth.net

animal.description:
Becca is a 2-year old dog with a hard start to life. She was found walking in the middle of a street in a poor Mexican village while in labor. She was so disproportionately enlarged, with pups pressing out from her abdomen at all angles, that it was hard to look at her without crying. As soon as she arrived at a Bone Voyage foster house it was immediately evident that she needed a vet. Luckily there was a kind vet who waited for her arrival and cared for her through the birth of 12 pups (8 of which were born dead). The pups were very large, thus accounting for her looking so disproportionately enlarged. 

The vet performed surgery believing there was a dead pup left and spayed her at the same time. The pups were raised by an experienced bottle feeder but only one survived. Becca spent two weeks loving life in a private courtyard of her own. Despite her living in an outside area she never soiled unless taken out for that purpose. 

Although minor compared to her pregnancy, it is worth noting that some jerks cut her ears believing that she looked like a cow and would look even more like a cow with different shaped ears. She is beautiful despite this, although it is painful to think of her experiencing that horror. 

Despite her struggle, she is a loving girl who is now at a board and train facility where she is getting along with a large pack of dogs at daycare and a smaller but still considerable size pack at home during the night. She is happy to be sleeping in bed with the daughter of her trainer and hopes to find a loving home of her own.

Currently in Mexico

YOU MAY BE REQUIRED TO QUARANTINE UPON PICK UP. PLEASE TAKE THIS INTO CONSIDERATION AND DO NOT APPLY IF YOU CANNOT QUARANTINE

animal.description:
Dog Name: Ares

Sex: Female 

Breed: Pit mix 

Age: 4 years old 

Weight: 75 pounds 

Medical Needs: None. Just coordinating with the vet to set up her spay which should be soon. 

Housebroken: Yes not a single accident. She will alert you if she has to go potty immediately. 

Crate trained: Yes. Her previous owner trained her to be left out of a crate and she does great. I have put her in a kennel for a little bit to see how she does and she has no problem with it walks right in lays down and goes to sleep 

Good in the car: Yes.

Good on a leash: Yes she walks fine on a leash. Every once in a while she might pull slightly put I correct her and she remembers how to walk. 

Energy level: Medium

Need a fenced in yard: Not really needed but she would love one! She loves to be outside chasing balls, running around, and being goofy 

Dog Friendly: Yes loves other dogs 

If yes, does your foster need another dog in its adoptive home? No 

Cat Friendly? No!

Kid Friendly: she absolutely adores kids. Shes currently in a foster home with a 4 year old and a 5 month old. She loves to do tricks and run around with the 4 year old. And the 5 month old well ares could lay with her and lick drool and milk off her face all day and be as happy as could be 

If yes, what's the youngest child you'd recommend they be placed with? Any age. Ares is very smart and very calm near the kids. Because of her size I would keep an eye on her if shes running around as she could accidentally knock a kid over but she would never hurt them on purpose. 

Special traits that make your foster special or that we need to know about them?

Ares came to us as a surrender. She was very well loved before coming to us and is very smart. Ares knows sit, stay, down, and paw (which she absolutely loves doing). she loves to spend her days cuddled up with you as you scratch her belly and she lounges around the house and her nights chasing a ball or running zoomies outside. Shes a calm girl but she also knows how to wrestle around and play when you get her going. Ares is a very goofy little dog and has us cracking up laughing everyday when she shows her goofy tricks. She loves being near her humans and other dogs and will do almost anything you ask for a yummy treat or a squeaky toy. Ares knows she is a princess and requires an extra special family that will love her to death, scratch her belly at least three times a day, and will feed her yummy yummy treats. If you think you can fufill her three simple wishes then come on over to grrde.org and fill out an application.

Meet Holly Jolly!

Holly is an absolute sweetheart! Holly is about 10 months old and approx 55 lbs estimated. She is a Lab/Pittie mix. She absolutely loves people,cats, and dogs and overall loves everyone!She is curious and very friendly. She loves to play fetch and would love to have a yard to run around and play in. She is such a cuddle bug bug and would love to go on beautiful hike with her new family.She is a ready to go girl and always ready to go on new adventures.She would be the best adventure partner. She is a smart and happy go lucky girl.She is very loving and she thinks shes a little lap dog.She loves car rides and would love a pup cup at Starbucks as a treat. She has tons of energy and would be well suited in a family with an active lifestyle. She would love another brother or sister to run around and play with that can match her energy. She is not quite potty trained, but she is a fast learner and would be able to get it down quickly.She is eager to please and willing. She has floppy ears that make her so adorable.She is excited to meet her new home in the PNW!

She is up to date on vaccines according to age, has received proper deworming, and comes with additional dewormer if needed. This pet is microchipped, spayed/neutered, comes with 2-6 months of Heartworm preventative, and one month free trial of pet insurance if registered by adopter with insurance company. All animals receive a health certificate (stating that a licensed veterinarian saw the pet and deemed it healthy for travel, but is not a promise of perfect health.) Our transports are USDA certified and the cost of transport is included in adoption fee! She is currently being fostered in Houston, TX but will be traveling to the PNW on 2/06.

animal.description:
Clark is am amazing little guy thats roughly a year old! He does awesome with other dogs and enjoys playing with them and showing them all of his fun beagle noises he can make. And boy, can he make the beagle noises! He loves chew toys and chasing down toys but doesnt always return them to play fetch. Sharing in caring Clark! When hes done playing and its time to nap he loves to be on the couch cuddled up on his person's lap. Hes working hard on his manners and training. Clark is potty trained and does really well with going outside. Clark is in the process of completing an extensive training to help him correct some behaviors he developed from being shuffled around from place to place. A perfect family for Clark would be a family who is invested in continuing Clarks training. Clark gets along great with other dogs and cats. Clark is a little apprehensive as he has never had a loving home, therefore he would do best in a home with no or older children.

He will make an awesome companion and best friend for a future family that loves all of the traits and fun that comes with a beagle! 

Clark is up to date on all shots, is heart worm free, neutered and micro-chipped. His adoption fee is $300, he is fostered in the Omaha area. Applications can be filled out at bassetandbeagle.org.

IF YOU ARE INTERESTED IN ADOPTING PLEASE CONTACT PIKE PET PALS ON FACEBOOK TO SET UP AN APPOINTMENT. IF "PENDING" IS BY THE DOG'S NAME IT MEANS THE DOG AS A PENDING ADOPTER APPOINTMENT.

This dog is 4-5 years old, weighs 57 pounds and available for 1/25/2021

This dog has been wormed for roundworms and hookworms and vaccinated with a 5 way vaccination on 1/29/2021

This dog has been vaccinated for rabies on 1/29/2021

This dog has received a flea and tick treatment on 1/29/2021

Altered? NO

Microchip found? NO

How dog arrived at the pound: Found as a stray

Pike Pet Pals assists in helping dogs get out of the Pike County Pound. Private adopters can visit the Pike County Dog Pound at 2575 Alma Omega Road Waverly, Ohio from 10am-2pmMonday through Friday. Saturday and Sundays by appointment. We recommend calling ahead to make sure the deputy on duty is not on an emergency call. 740-947-5996

Rescues can contact Volunteer Julie at pikepetpals@gmail.com . For the fastest response please message us on our Pike Pet Pals Facebook page. Please visit our website at www.pikedogs.petfinder.com for information on adoptions.

Adoption fee is $50.00 cash. This fee includes a Rabies vaccination, 5 in 1 vaccination, worming for roundworms and hookworms, Capstar, flea and tick treatment and a current Ohio dog license.

Dogs are vetted at the dog pound. We do not guarantee a dog's health. Please take your newly adopted dog to a veterinarian as soon as possible. If you do not have a regular veterinarian we -recommend Chillicothe Animal Clinic, 1100 Eastern Avenue, Chillicothe, Ohio 45601, 740-773-4133

To donate for vetting and vaccinations please click on the Sponsor Me link. All donations are used for emergency vetting, routine vet work and vaccinations for the dogs housed at the Pike County Dog Pound.

animal.description:
Hi meet Mari,

Mari is a lovely Boxer mix, she is 1 year old. Mari is supper energetic. She loves playing with her toys . She is a happy go lucky girl with with everyone she meets. She would like a home that will take her on adventures, continue her socialization, and give her lots of love. She wants a person or family who will provide her with a life a mental and physical stimulation while keeping her safe and happy. 

Mari came to us as an owner surrender but by no fault of her owner. 

We hold an event every weekend at our facility on SATURDAY 11-5pm.   Please visit our social media platforms for the specifics for each weekend as it changes from week to week. Please find our application at lovejoyfoundation.org when you come to an event please bring that filled out in hand with you. You can find our application at Lovejoyfoundation.orgYou MUST submit an APPLICATION via email in hopes to get an appointment, our application is found on our website lovejoyfoundation.org. If you do not get a phone call by Friday then we did not have anything available for you or the pet of interest was adopted before we got you application. We are a Southern California based rescue and do nothing adopt further than an hour from our headquarters in Inglewood, Ca. we do not adopt out more than a 30 minute radius. We appreciate you being understanding and Patient as we attempt to go back to a new normal.

*This dog is in Texas and will be coming to Ontario early February*Please apply to adopt at reddogrescue.org*
Hello, my name is Alice May! I'd like to say that I am an incredible girl. I am full of love and Im seeking a special family to share the joys of my life alongside. I really love cuddling, but most importantly, I want to play with my toys and go on exciting adventures with my family. I am very protective of unknown outside noise and am never hesitant to let you know by gentle barking at the door. Along my journey, Ive enjoyed play dates with other dogs, meeting new people, and playing with Doggy IQ toys and bones. Ohhh, bones are my absolute favourite. I get cold easily, so I love having a blanket to cuddle. I can be clingy sometimes, and sometime will get upset if left alone from my humans for fur siblings. Im elated to meet my forever family and share all my love and joy for life with them.
*The picture with the cone is after her spay.

This adorable boy is going to be a big guy and will need a home with a full femced yard and we would prefer a family with experience on big breeds. He is currently being fostered with other dogs, cats and kids and we are requiring the adopter to continue his socialization and involve him in training throughout his life to make sure he is kept social and happy. Make sure you are ready to spend time and finances for training, supplies and arw ready to commit for the life of the dog before applying. Do you have a yard? Do you have the means to enroll him in training and comtimue his socialization? Do you have the space he needs now AND as an adult/senior? 

HE IS NOT POTTY TRAINED. His foster is working with him diligently but he is only 9 weeks old. As expected it will take a bit until he is considered fully potty trained and as such, it ultimately is the responsibility of an adopter to potty train if they choose to adopt a PUPPY.

*Animal is AVAILABLE. TO APPLY FOR ADOPTION OR IF YOU HAVE ADDITIONAL QUESTIONS THAT ARE NOT ADDRESSED IN THIS PROFILE, visit our website mutthutrescues.org Click on 'Adoptables', and click on the animal's Picture to view Full Profile, Additional Information, Pictures and Stats. An application is required in order to apply for the animal and set up a Meet & Greet if your application is chosen. Once we close our application intake period, we review all applications and choose the best one, out of many, to set up a meet. This process is lengthy, and may take a few days or a few weeks.

animal.description:
Introducing Zuzu, the cutest, sweetest, little hippo you will ever meet! Shes a compact 2 y.o., 45lb bundle of love looking for a forever family. She s snuggling, kisses, walks, and following her humans around the house wherever they go. Zuzu is truly a gentle soul - Just look into her big beautiful brown eyes and pet her velvety soft smooshy face and youll see!
She has some limitations with her hips and hind legs, so a home with carpeted stairs (or none at all) is a must. She can handle the few steps off the porch into the yard at her foster home. Shes good with other dogs and loves a good game of tug of war with her foster brother, but shes on the calmer side, not interested in running around much. She ADORES children. No cats.
Zuzu is heartworm positive, therefore she would be placed in a foster-to-adopt situation within reasonable driving distance to the hospital in S Jersey where she will receive treatment beginning next month.
During her treatment, she could begin her furever as your velvety angel!

animal.description:
Harken is a wonderful, young boy who has come so far in such a short amount of time! Although found as a stray, and not clear if he had ever lived in a home, worn a collar or walked on a leash, he is now calmly walking on a leash, taking treats like a gentleman and happily living indoors. Harken’s best friend in the world is a tiny, 4 pound chihuahua :) He loves to play with his little pal and is so gentle! He is playfully curious with cats, but leaves them alone for the most part. He’ll need proper introductions, time and space to warm up to big dogs in the home and has done well meeting new people and children. Older kids, who are steady on their feet, will be a good fit for this guy. Harken loves to sleep belly-up in tight spaces and will make sure you have proper “help” in the bathroom :) Harken is looking for a Pyr-experienced family, as he can be quite the Houdini at times. He is showing some mild, early signs of hip dysplasia in one hip, so his new family should be committed to keeping him at a healthy weight. Harken loves leisurely walks, without any big obstacles, and loves getting attention from his humans. He will give you the famous Pyr Paw to indicate he wants more pets or scratches. Harken is a wonderful boy, who’s come so far and still has so much potential - if he sounds like the Pyrfect boy for your family, apply for him today!

NYS Registered Rescue # RR102
NGPR dogs are in foster homes throughout the U.S., NOT Beacon, NY. View full listing, fee and online application at - www.nationalpyr.org/adoptable-dogs (sorry, no phone submissions, but if you would like more information you can email us at renpyrgroup@yahoo.com).

Secure VISIBLE fencing is required; invisible fencing WILL NOT contain this breed.

Our goal is to assess every application on its own merits. Key considerations are: 1) the experience of the applicant with large breed dogs 2) children in the household or regularly visiting the household are ready for a large-breed dog who is a guardian by nature (www.nationalpyr.org/know-the-breed) and 3) the sex of other dogs currently residing in the household to avoid same-sex aggression issues. For puppies under six months old, the applicant’s ability to socialize the puppy with older dogs is a priority.

Please consider Paco when you are looking for your next family member and companion!

animal.description:
*NOTE* Applications for Ripley are now closed. Thank you to all who applied! 

We will reply to all applicants, but we ask for your patience as we review the applications.  


** TORONTO AREA ADOPTERS ONLY**

Meet Ripley:
Ripley is a beautiful shepherd mix puppy new to our rescue. She came to us from Northern Manitoba. We don’t know her birthday but the vet feels she is about four months old. She weighs 27 pounds.

Ripley is a very sweet puppy with a lot of potential. At this time, she is extremely fearful of humans. It is evident that she did not have exposure to humans before her rescue.
She is slowly adapting to her foster home but will need an experienced adopter who is patient and understanding of fearful dogs. Her foster mom tells us that Ripley is very well behaved despite her young age. Ripley sleeps through the night and is making good progress with her housetraining.
Her foster parents provide lots of positive training and Ripley is becoming more confident. She requires an adopter who will take the time to gain Ripley’s trust and continue with positive, reward based training.

We feel she is best suited to a quiet, calm adult home (children 12 years +). 
Due to her fearfulness we consider Ripley a high flight risk.
For that reason, she must always be walked on leash and we recommend an adopter in a house with a safely fenced back yard. Adopters will have to follow our special safety guidelines.

Ripley gets along well with the other dogs in her foster home and loves to play.

She is an active puppy and requires plenty of daily exercise.

Ripley is in good health. She has had deworming but is still being treated for parasites. Her adopter will need to followup on this. She had her first puppy vaccination and will require her second and third booster. Since she is not fully vaccinated Ripley can not be around a lot of dogs. It is not safe for her to be at a dog park yet. She is microchipped. 

Please see our website for more information on our adoption program and adoption application. (www.adoptadogsavealife.com)
She is in a foster home in Toronto. Our adoption process includes an online application, a telephone interview, a virtual home visit and a meeting with the dog. Her adoption fee is $450 and we require a $200 spay deposit.

animal.description:
Sandy is "Foster to Adopt," as she is awaiting a dental and mass removal on 2/24.

If you are looking for a great dog that is calm, easy going, and loves to cuddle, Sandy is your girl! Sandy is a 12.5 year old Yellow Lab that was surrendered to Grey Face for medical reasons. Sandy is almost ready to be adopted, but is just waiting on a dental extraction and a mass removal, scheduled for late February, which is why Sandy is labeled as "Foster to Adopt." Overall, Sandy is a pretty typical senior Lab. Sandy loves eating, sleeping, and going for walks. She especially loves her humans, following them around and waiting for snuggles. Her foster paw-rents describe her as the "perfect dog."

Age: 12.5 years old

Breed:
Yellow Labrador

Weight:
65lbs

Kid-friendly:
Potentially kid friendly, but has never lived with children. Likely, older-considerate children would be OK.

Dogs:
Has lived with other dogs, does well with them. Mostly ignores other dogs on walks.

Cats:
Has lived with cats. Mostly ignores them.

Crate trained:
Not using crates in foster home.

Potty trained:
Yes

Likes:
Humans, car rides, treats, large balls, stuffed toys, sleeping, eating, and playing

Health concerns:
Scheduled for a tooth extraction, and needs special food for Kidney Disease

Adoption fee:
$275

Our dogs receive heartworm and flea/tick prevention the first week of each month, March through November. Dogs that have stage 3 or 4 dental disease will receive a dental procedure in rescue. We aspirate all lumps and remove those that our veterinary partners suggest removing.

Adopters will be responsible for continued preventatives, follow-up appointments, and medications (if applicable).

$50 discount for seniors (65+) and veterans. Adoption fees help pay for the dog's veterinary exam, vaccinations (rabies, distemper, and bordetella), HW test, blood panel, a microchip, and spay/neuter if needed and additional health needs specific to each animal.

You can apply to adopt at www.greyfacerescue.org/adoption-application

animal.description:
{s3829code380/}
If you would like to provide this dog a loving home, please fill out a pre-adoption application.

Have a question? Please read our Frequently Asked Questions and Adoption Processed Explained documentation.
_________ B I O ______________

Name:Evie
Size: ~Medium range: 26-60 lbs
Adoption Donation:$250 (applicable sales tax included).Adoption fees may be paid by cash or check.
Other:Spayed Female, Vaccinations current, Microchip

Eviejust wants your luv!

Foster Home Feedback

1/29/21: Evie does best in a home with another playful dog, otherwise she has shown to be destructive. She doesn't like her kennel and is left out with my large dogs and does well. Evie loves to play with my Boxer mix. Without some sort of exercise and stimulation, she gets destructive. She likes to be super bossy to my Boxer mix and he lets her, so a more laid back doggie friend would be best. She will steal his toys and he lets her. My large Pit doesn't like her sassiness and had a tiff with her, but she had some pent up energy that she needed to get out. Everyone is good and is happy again. All the dogs sleep with us in our bedroom with no problems. Overall, Evie is a sweet dog and loves to snuggle with her people and other dogs.

1/6/21: Evie is tiny. She looks like a cross between a Boston Terrier and a
pocket Pittie. I forgot to tell you she got a bath and did wonderfully.
She didn't like it but sat nicely and waited to be done. She took just a few days to learn our routine and hasn't had any accidents in days. She does bark at noises and now barks in her kennel so it takes some time for her to settle, but she is getting the hang of it. She just wants to be with me and my dogs. She follows me everywhere. Evie has not gotten into anything she shouldn't.

She chews on bones or toys that are readily available. She tries to steal toys from my other dogs. She has some sass and will snark at my other pups, which my dogs just look at her like she is crazy. She is learning to not do
that and is following my direction well. Evie is so smart and listens
well. She does snore once she really relaxes, not loud but preciously content.

Overall, Evie is a pretty easy foster. She doesn't jump on me and gets fed well with others. She does take treats a little rough but does well around other dogs doing it. She does well at feeding time, I fed her separately at first but now she just hangs out and waits for her dinner with the other dogs. She knows to sit to be fed. Oh, and Evie is an expert snuggler. She slept with us last night and she slept snuggled in all night long.

1/3/21: This little pocket Pittie is the cutest. Evie follows me around and gets along with my three dogs (Chihuahua, Pit, and Boxer) and the cat. She slept in her kennel without a peep. This is her first day so more to come as we learn more about her.To view additional dogs available for adoption, please see our website: www.4luvofdog.org

animal.description:
Meet Darla! Darla is about 1 year old and a very sweet and active girl! She is a 15 pound terrier mix who was was rescued from Mexico and is now spayed, microchipped, vaccinated, and looking for her forever family. She gets along with other dogs but is a dominant female so would do best with a submissive male  as her partner in crime. Darla is still learning basic commands and leash walking. She is doing very well with potty training and loves to be with her person whether it’s snuggling on the couch or going on a walk.

We suggest a home with children over the age of 10 for this dog. This dog cannot be adopted out of state. Please see our home page for a list of our Saturday adoption sites. Every potential adopter is required to fill out an adoption application and the dog is placed in the home that would be most suitable for the dog. We do not place our dogs in homes with unfenced swimming pools. Generally we don't release the dogs at the adoption site that day except on occasion to former adopters. 

If you are interested in adopting this dog, please email FCIAadoptions@aol.com or call 619-466-9137. Due to the pandemic we are now requiring all interested people to fill out our application at www.FCIAnimals.org. If we think it is a good match, we will arrange an introduction.

animal.description:
Hi, I'm Freckles! I'm a sweet and social border collie searching for a loving home to call my own! I've got a purple dot because I don't care to share my tasty treats, and I'm not very friendly with other animals. I would be best suited to an experienced dog owner with no children at home because I need a lot of training and exercise! Don't let my age deceive you; in typical border collie fashion, I don't show any signs of slowing down. I'm definitely a very people-oriented dog, so if you have experience training dogs in the past, I think you and I will have lots of fun! If you understand my breed and you think we would be a good match, please pay me a visit soon.

What's HW+? I'm currently being treated for heartworms. I'll need to keep a calm lifestyle until finished and may require an appointment or two. Please don't be deterred, my lifespan isn't shortened, and I'm not contagious to your other pets.

Take me on a Slumber Party! You can bring me home for a 3 day - 30 day trial period. HSSC will provide food, medications, and necessities. If I'm not the one for you, just bring me back to HSSC and provide feedback on what would be the best home for me.

animal.description: If you're looking for a dog who likes to go, go, go, look no further. Prince loves to run as fast as he can in the yard, stopping every once in a while to make sure you're still watching him. He gets super excited to go on walks and pulls a little, but luckily he's small enough that he doesn't make much headway. He'll definitely benefit from continued work on his leash manners. Prince will do best in a home where he can get a daily walk and play time. Once he's worn out, Prince is a sweet little lap dog. He climbs right onto you and does that cute dog thing where he turns a couple circles before finally settling in. He loves to unwind with a gentle back scratch and some ear rubs. Prince is looking for a quiet, adult only home, with few visitors. He may do best as the only dog, but if you do have another dog in the home, Prince will want to meet him to be sure it is a good fit. This prince also wants a castle, so no apartment life for him. Come meet this little ham! Prince is a Diamond Dogs and will be shown by appointment only. Diamond Dogs are dogs that are currently receiving special training from staff and volunteers through our behavior modification program. If you are interested in learning more about this animal, please fill out an application by clicking here . Be sure to include Prince A1333782 when filling out the survey. After reviewing your application, we will only be reaching out to you if the animal is a good fit for your home.

animal.description: Hi, Im Sparkles! Im a 4 month old Lab Chihuahua mix, and Im 7 pounds right now. Im very playful and sweet, and give the best snuggles. I am working really hard to learn as much as I can, before going to my forever home. Potty training is a work in progress, but I know if youre patient with me, Ill get it figured out really soon! I sleep in my crate at night, but I dont always like it... Im really good with kids, and love to play with the big dog in my foster home. Im still learning what is and isnt for me to chew on, but Im sure you will help me with that too! I would love more than anything, to come be a part of your family, if you would let me! Sparkles' adoption fee is $400 which covers her spay, vaccinations appropriate at the time of adoption, microchip and any additional medical care she may have needed while in the rescues care. We are a foster based rescue, we do not house dogs at a facility. Age and breed, are NLR's best guess as we often don't know who or what mom and dad are. If you are interested in adopting, please fill out an application on our website www.northernlakesrescue.org

animal.description:
Hannah is quite the sweetie.   This  6 or 7  year old female had a tough start. For her first 6 years (or so) she was a breeder dog for a puppy mill in Lancaster County.  When she no longer was breeding full and viable litters she was one of the lucky dogs we were able to pull into our rescue. 
Hannah is much enjoying her retirement in her foster home near Philadelphia. She is not terribly active but she loves walks . She likes to watch TV on the sofa and just be with her people. 
She likes to play with the other dogs in the house and she is appropriate when meeting and interacting with other dogs.  With cats she will chase but she doesn't seem to be aggressive about it. 
Hannah gets nervous in crowds of people and can be  leery of some people but overall she is friendly with most adults. She can be picked up and handled ,  Her toe nails can be cut  and her teeth safely checked.  The only thing Hannah doesn't like is children. which could be lack of exposure but more probably past history when she was a breeding dog. 
As Hannah's foster , I can assure you she will be a dear companion for someone just looking for a buddy.  She's  healthy and doesn't need alot of attention.  She is content just to be loved
MAJR is a small foster based rescue . All of our dogs live with foster families. We do not have a kennel where you can meet the dogs. Hannah is currently in  the Philadelphia  suburbs . If you are interested in adopting Hannah please fill out an adoption application on our website MAJR.org

Meet Winnie-

Winnie is a sweet, goofy little puppy. She loves to play with her sister and our resident dog. Chewing on bones or stuffed toys is some of her favorite things to do . She likes to chew. She’s learning to go to the bathroom outside and on the potty pads.  She’s a bit more of a go with the flow puppy and would be a wonderful addition to any home!

animal.description:
Robbie is a one year old, spayed female, Border Collie mix.  Border 
Collie's are notorious for being one of the smartest dog breeds and Robbie is no exception.  She is extremely intelligent!  She has done very well with training basics such as "sit", "come", "stay", and "lie down" and picked all of it up in record time.  Robbie is a very sweet dog, however, she prefers playtime more than anything!  She is very much a herder and loves to run around in circles whether it be to chase her own tail or a toy.  She loves toys of all shapes and sizes.  She is very good with other dogs and we believe that she craves the companionship of them.  She would most likely do best in a home with another dog (or more) to run around with, play with, and bond with.  She is a very friendly girl and soaks up attention like a sponge!  Robbie will need either an active family or one with a large fenced in area for her to run around and let her energy out.  She will need a family that understands the amount of stimulation that she will need to keep her happy and healthy.  Basically, someone that has the time to run and play with her.  Meet and greets at our shelter are currently by appointment only.  If you are interested in meeting Robbie, please call us at the shelter at (828) 488-0418.

animal.description: Meet Hotdog! His New Year's resolution is to make 2021 the year of health and fitness. Hotdog came to us with a few extra pounds that he's looking to shed. He would love a semi-active owner that is consistent with his fitness regimen so he can drop some pounds and live a happier healthier life. Don't let his size fool you, this boy can be very playful (and we expect his personality and activity level to shine brighter once he loses some weight). He loves to flop in front of anyone that will let him to get some belly rubs. This happy-go-lucky guy will do just about anything for a treat, and loves toys, but doesn't always like to share his items. If he goes to a home with children, they should be older, mature children that respect his boundaries. Hotdog is excited to be the only animal in the home, so he doesn't have to share his people either! If you have room in your home and heart for this silly boy, come in and meet Hotdog today!

animal.description:
Hey there, I'm Pamela! Aren't I a cutie with my big eyes and beautiful grey and white coat? I am about 2 years old, 45-ish pounds, and overall a very happy gal. I can be quite active and love playing fetch--most of the time I will even bring the ball back to you to throw again. I am not bothered by cats or other dogs. I do however get jealous if there is another doggie who is getting attention and I am not, or if there are people who could be petting me and are not (I will let you know by whining a bit but will eventually quiet down). 

I enjoy car rides and looking out the window. I am an absolute sucker for some pets and scratches and take treats nicely. I do need some work with leash training, but I have no problem being on a leash--harnesses work best with me as I tend to pull. I have been told that I am a very smart girl who learns fast. I have not been tested around children, but I would likely do fine with older kids. If you are looking for a sweet, fun pup to be a new member of your family, then look no further!

animal.description:
Cruiser is an avid eater who enjoys dropping down into "sit if he thinks he will get a reward for it. While he doesn't enjoy the crate quite yet, he is good about going into it, especially when given treats or a meal in it. Cruiser has had no accidents in the house or his crate. At first, Cruiser was scared of the garage door noise, as well as the stairs. However, he quickly figured out that the garage door wasn't a monster and that stairs are fun! (He gets a good amount of exercise now running up and down the stairs multiple times a day.) His foster mom is also teaching him "off and "go back, so he understands boundaries and where he can and can't be in the house. Cruiser has gone on several adventures with his foster mom, including the pet store. He was an excellent passenger; he just laid down on the floor and never barked. He was interested in being a co-pilot whenever the car stopped, however. Cruiser has been excited to meet some dogs, and less excited about others. Cruiser's favorite toy is a nylabone. If you are interested in meeting this sweet boy, please submit an appointment request here: 

https://forms.office.com/Pages/ResponsePage.aspx?id=lsJ_8Hpq8k2OaDbCdJiGnZ0KUdNlMOxGs9o3MWhive1UOFRNUUhQMlFUSlM4UU04RUdEQ1dQNUFWTC4u

Woof! My name is Jeff. I'm a 5 year old, mixed breed boy who is ready to go home! I am 55 pounds, neutered, vaccinated, microchipped and heartworm tested. My adoption fee is $99
In response to the social distancing recommendations from the CDC and WHO, the Roanoke Valley SPCA is modifying our adoption procedures. With these new restrictions, we do our best to be as fair as possible. Pets are adopted on a first come basis. Our challenge is to find homes for the pets in our care as quickly as possible so we can help other pets in need. With the increase in cases in Southwest Virginia, adoption hours are Thursday-Saturday between Noon and 7 pm. Unfortunately, we are unable to hold pets nor guarantee a pet will be available at the time of your appointment, but we do promise to call you if a pet is adopted prior to your appointment.
If you are interested in adopting me, please compete our online Adoption Application. Please book your appointment to meet me. Our adoption staff will give you a call to confirm the appointment and answer any questions you may have prior to the meet and greet.
Call 540-339-9247 Monday - Saturday between Noon and 7 pm to speak with an adoption counselor for more information

animal.description:
Percy is an inquisitive, playful, loving little girl. Her interests include treat puzzles, naps, zoomies, and sunbathing. Percy's most distinguishing features include big, perky ears and a smile that takes up her whole face. If you happen to be up for training and brain games, then Percy is your match. She already knows many commands, is eager to continue learning and loves treats! Given her height, she may try to stick her snoot in your treat pouch to sneak some snacks - she is such a silly girl!
Percy is ready for a home to call her own. Could it be yours? Come meet this sweet girl! Please fill out our Online Questionnaire for mor Information.

animal.description: Steve is absolutely adorable. He loves to let his opinions be known. He is very friendly with people. He enjoys affection and likes to be with people. I don't think he's housebroken and I'm not sure he's ever been inside before. He was abandoned with his brother in a yard when the owners moved out. They didn't have a dog house, just a plastic crate for shelter. They both have some food aggression issues, possibly because food was scarce and they learned to guard it from each other. Both of these little boys will become amazing pets in no time. They are thrilled with the changes in their lives so far, and once they get to be inside a home they'll be even more thrilled. They can not be placed together (they have some issues with each other) but they are ok with other dogs for the most part. They are bossy, they want to be in charge with other dogs...but other than that they are ok. At Autumn Acres Animal Rescue we believe each individual animal matters. We take in special cases some of which will stay with us as a sanctuary dog.If the animal is listed as a Socially Imperfect Dog this means they have special needs and special requirements for potential adopters.If the animal is listed as a Socially Imperfect RESIDENT this animal is NOT available for adoption and is one of our sanctuary residents. We list them on our sites because they still matter and they still need donations to help with their long term care.Check out our website for more information: http://www.autumnacres.org

animal.description:
Dexter was born in May 2020, and is a true ball of energy! He is beautiful, brilliant and a complete wild child.

Dexter came to us with a severely broken leg. Months of casts and limited activity allowed him to heal beautifully, but for a young, energetic dog, it was a tough start to life. As a result, he has not been socialized the way we would like, and has months of pent up energy to work off. 

This dog is the full package, but he really needs an owner that is very experienced with the GSD breed. They are strong willed, extremely smart and stubborn as mules. They are also devoted, loving dogs that are the best of companions in the right home.

We don't know how Dexter will be with other dogs, children or cats. He will definitely need a large securely fenced yard. Experience with working breed dogs is strongly preferred.


Our dogs are fed a nutrient rich dog food named NutriSource.  Our experience is a high quality dog food keeps vet bills down and well-being high.

If you have any questions please email: claudiaatwag@gmail.com

Visit our website to fill out an Adoption Application  http://www.wagsequimwa.com

Adoption donation fee $350  (Please understand this adoption donation goes towards helping all the dogs we rescue)

animal.description:
Oh how we love this dog! Marky is a 3 year old Mastiff that has been blind since birth. He is huge, beautiful, loving, smart and strong!

Marky came to us when his owner was no longer able to care for him. He has settled in well and is full of joy and playfulness. Because he cannot see at all, he is easily frighten and is only now confident enough to take short walks on a leash without being terrified. He does great in our play yards once he gets a sense of them.

Because of his size and high fear response, we feel he needs to be in a home without young children. He might enjoy a calm doggy friend, but no small or high energy dogs. Cats are a definite no as are stairs in the home.

Marky must have a securely fenced yard to run and play in. Leash walking might always be difficult for him, so having a safe place to just be a young happy dog is crucial.

This is a special dog, that deserves a special home. Maybe yours?

Our dogs are fed a nutrient rich dog food named NutriSource.  Our experience is a high quality dog food keeps vet bills down and well-being high.

animal.description:
Hi! My name is Audrey! I'm a pit/shepherd mix, 1.5 years old (Born 7-11-2019), 60 lbs, & I have a black & white coloring.

I was originally born here quite a while ago. It was me, my mom Oreo, & my 12 other siblings. We were all "Cookie" puppies at the time, but I've had this name for a lot longer now. There were a couple of us that didn't make it due to parvo, but most of us made it through alive & well! That was a long time ago, though. Since then I've been in my new home, but for a while now I've had issues with other animals, mostly dogs. We've lived together before, but every once in a while I'll just decide to pick a fight out of nowhere, so it's not a 100% all the time sort of thing, but probably best if I just didn't go to a home with other animals to avoid any issues. Otherwise, I'm great with people! I'm super high energy, I love to run, & play fetch, & just anything that gets me up, out, & moving! I may have my problems, just like any shelter dog, but I promise I'll make a great companion for you or your family if you're willing to give me a chance!

I've been spayed, but I'll need to get an updated rabies shot before I can leave. If you're looking for a rough & rowdy girl that can play with you all day, come check me out sometime!

Izzy is an approximately one year old female, who loves to play and loves people! She is spayed and has even had a gastropexy procedure to help prevent bloating. Izzy is current on vaccines and Heartworm preventative.

A fenced yard is essential.  Weimaraners typically have a high prey drive, so smaller pets may not be a good fit; however, Izzy may do well with another larger, calm dog.  Unknown with children, but perhaps gentle, dog-savvy youngsters might work.  Izzy will come to a new home with toys and her favorite dog bed.

Living with someone who is home most of the time would probably be best for Izzy.  She is afraid of small dark places such as a closed bathroom or closet and did not do well with a crate.  Izzy had a bit of a rough puppyhood; but she is young and so ready to learn and love!!  With consistency and patience, Izzy will be a wonderful companion!

animal.description:
Hi! My name in Brownie! I'm a Boxer mix, 5 years old, 70 lbs, & I have a tan/black/white coloring.

I'm a spunky & lively guy who I know for a fact you'll fall in love with the moment you meet me! I've just got that sort of vibe to me, ya know? The type of thing that makes everyone around me just a bit more chill & happy, & always puts a smile on their face! I might have some grey on my face now, but don't let that fool you! I've still got plenty of juice left in me! I love to get outside, run around, & I'm ALWAYS up for some fetch! I haven't had a ton of socialization with kids or other animals, & while I've never had an issue with adults at all at least, I don't really get along with other animals that well. Or, like, at all to be honest. Especially when it comes to there being food around! I'll definitely need to be in a one-animal home, but it'd probably be best if it were a home with all adults as well. I've always been sort of an indoor/outdoor dog who was able to come & go from home, so who knows what I might've done out there! Well, of course, I know what I've done, but that's my own little secret! Being I've been a partial outdoor dog, you'll definitely need to keep me on leash for a good while when you bring me home. I might have the tendency to wander off, maybe jump a fence or somethin. Who knows!? I might end up getting into a little trouble here & there, but if you're able to teach me to stick around better & give me a loving new home, I promise I'll be a great dog for you for years to come!

I'm up to date on shots, neutered, chipped, & ready to go! I also tested negative for heartworm. If you're looking for a handsome guy who's got the charm to back it up, I'm the dog for you!

animal.description:
This dog is in Tennessee. Adoption Donation $200 if picked up in TN, $250 plus transport fee for out of state adoptions.

Meet Rico! This adorable and friendly fellow is a 5-to-6-year-old, 13 pound Chihuahua / Dachshund mix who is a champion snuggler. Rico likes to cuddle, and his foster mom says he prefers the lifestyle of a lap dog. Rico will give you sweet canine kisses if you promise to trade for some belly rubs. He does great with other dogs and also cats. Rico likes to go for walks, and also enjoys quiet time too, just as long as he is with you! His favorite spot is curled up under the covers in bed. Rico is crate trained and doing well with housetraining as long as he gets frequent outings and uses a belly band in the house. Rico has heartworms and is on the mend from treatment for those; he needs a calm and relaxing home to complete his recovery. If you feel you can help this precious pooch find the life he deserves, apply to adopt!

Interested in adopting? Take the first step and complete an adoption application on our website: http://aarf-tn.com/adopt/adoption-apps/

If you have questions that are not covered in the profile, visit the Pet Inquiry Form: http://aarf-tn.com/contact/pet-inquiry-form/.

THIS PET IS FOSTERED IN TENNESSEE! We do list and adopt our pets nationwide. Typical transport cost to the Northeast is $160. Due to interstate adoption regulations, we are not able to adopt to RI and MA state residents.

A.A.R.F. (All About Rescue and Fixin' Inc.) http://aarf-tn.com/ is a non-profit, 501(c)(3) no kill animal rescue organization located in the Upper Cumberland area of Tennessee. A.A.R.F. is comprised of unpaid volunteers and survives only on public donations. Thank you for thinking adoption first!

Prior to adoption, all canines and felines are spayed or neutered, have received their age appropriate vaccinations, have been de-wormed for common parasites, and have received treatment for prevention of fleas and ticks. All canines over the age of 6 months have been tested for heartworm. All canines are put on heartworm prevention as soon as possible - this means dogs as soon as they are tested negative. Puppies are put on prevention immediately. All felines, regardless of age, have been tested for Feline Leukemia/FIV. Each animal receives a health check by a licensed veterinarian prior to adoption. Anything else found will be treated by our organization prior to adoption.
